The American flag is a rectangular cloth with horizontal seven red and six white stripes. The dark blue canopy contains 50 five-pointed white stars.
Write a function named flagColors that takes a string color containing the name of the color and returns:
"This color is on the flag" if color is 'red', 'navy' or 'white';
"This color is not on the flag", otherwise.


function flagColors(color){
  return color === 'red' || color === 'navy' || color === 'white' ? 'This color is on the flag' : 'This color is not on the flag';
}
